    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 Engine Service Manual - Crankcase, Crankshaft, and Camshaft -
        Cleaning, Inspection, and Testing - Measuring Camshaft Bushings
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s15.3.6" svcproctype="measure" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Measuring Camshaft Bushings</title>
        <figure id="f3450015023" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd06/D0620.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Measurement of camshaft bushing inside diameter</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Telescoping gauge</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Outside micrometer</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>Inspect five camshaft bushings for wear and correct running clearance as follows:</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_325.xml" xrefid="s15.t3">telescoping gauge set</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s15.t3"/>
                and 2-3 inch micrometer to measure camshaft bushing inside diameters with bushings installed in
                crankcase.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To determine running clearance, subtract previous camshaft journal diameter readings from
                camshaft bushing inside diameter readings.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_323.xml" xrefid="s15.t1">maximum allowable running clearance is exceeded
                </hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s15.t1"/>, replace camshaft bushings. See
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_308.xml" xrefid="s15.2.7.ref1">camshaft bushing removal</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s15.2.7.ref1"/>
                in this section.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect each bushing bore in upper crankcase assembly for burrs or debris that could damage
                new bushings.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove burrs and clean bores thoroughly before installing new camshaft bushings.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
